# FRONT PAGE SEQUENCE BEGIN

>OVER BLACK



>**_SUPER: MITCH’S FIRST FRONT PAGE_**<



The Opening chords of “KISS AN ANGEL GOOD MORNING”--the CHARLIE PRIDE standard.

.OPENING MONTAGE - VARIOUS LOCATIONS

- Welcome to Nashville sign

- Drone footage of the Second Avenue Historic District

- Establishing shots of Nashville... The skyline silhouetted against the rising sun.

CONTROL
(on POLICE RADIO)
Ten-one hundred shots fired eighteen-eighty Belcourt Avenue, Belcourt Towers apartment number eight fifty-seven.

- The AT&T “BATMAN” BUILDING reflecting the rising sun.

CAR 58
(on POLICE RADIO)
Control, Roger Ten-one hundred. Car fifty-eight responding. Show ETA ten minutes.

- SHIRTLESS MAN jogs in VANDERBILT UNIVERSITY jogging shorts.

MITCH (V.O.)
Like everything else in his short life, Jimmy Chin Lee’s death was perfectly timed.

- A tired looking woman unlocks the door of her business. The sign above her reads PANCAKE PANTRY - DELIVERIES ONLY.

UNCLE ROSS (O.C.)
(singing)
~ You’ve got to...
~ Kiss an angel good morning
~ Let her know you think about her
~ When you’re gone

INT. HOUSE - MITCH’S ROOM - BEFORE SUNRISE

Dark: A streetlight cuts through the Venetian blinds. The windows are open but the gauzy drapes are still--no breeze.

CONTROL (RADIO)
Roger fifty-eight. En route to eighteen-eighty Belcourt Avenue showing E-T-A ten minutes. Control out.

In shadows me see him half-stand, half-stumble out of bed and Frankenstein to the bathroom, hitting his head on the door.

CAR 58 (RADIO)
Fifty-eight out.

We see him splash water on his face in shadows: The old fashioned fluorescent light in the bathroom takes a second to warm up.

MITCH (V.O.)
You always hate the celebrity that dies too close to deadline.

The bathroom light finally flickers on revealing: MITCH SAWYER (20's, M, At peace with the world being on fire) and he’s sweaty.

A slow-rotating ceiling fan doesn’t seem to be providing any relief from the heat.

He pulls on jeans, sniffs a shirt, putting it on, then shoes. 

He grabs his camera bag, throws on a NASHVILLE SOUNDS BALL CAP that hangs on a hook on the wall.

UNCLE ROSS (O.C.)
(singing)
~ m-m-m-m-m-m-m-m-- ...Kiss an angel good morning
~ And lover her like the devil
~ When you get back home

Mitch returns and grabs the **PORTABLE POLICE RADIO** sitting on the desk, his shirt already showing the start of pit-stains.

INT. HOUSE - FRONT DOOR - BEFORE SUNRISE

UNCLE ROSS (60’s, one foot in the grave, and one foot on a banana peel) in his skivvies sits in a large Lay-z-boy in the living room wearing giant KOSS headphones,

UNCLE ROSS (O.C.)
(singing)
~ la-la-la-mmmmmm--- ...Kiss an angel good morning.

Mitch passes him on the way out of the house.

UNCLE ROSS
(singing)
~ And love her like the devil
~ When you get back hooommmeeee...

The front screen door slams and we watch through a large picture window as Mitch gets into a VINTAGE VW BUG and drives in the pre-dawn streetlights.

EXT. NASHVILLE, TN - EARLY MORNING

Beauty shots of the city as the VW Bug drives through. 

The VW Bug passes a BILLBOARD FOR BELOVED OF GOD CHURCH with the tagline PASTOR PIKE LEWIS WELCOMES YOU featuring A smiling man in a suit with premature grey.

EXT. NASHVILLE, TN - EARLY MORNING

.MITCH’S NIKON

Rounded edges, bracket lines and black matte around a 3:2 aspect ratio tells us we’re looking through the view-finder of a 35mm camera: 

A public street. A street-sign reads “Keep Nashville Clean: Don’t litter.”

CAR 58
(on POLICE RADIO O.S.)
Control, this is fifty-eight. We gotta ten-fifty-four, possible one-eight-seven. Request forensics, Sherlock and a slow bus at Belmont Towers apartment eight fifty-seven.

MITCH (V.O.)
The call came over the scanner at more than 10 hours before deadline.

CONTROL
(on police radio)
Roger fifty-eight. Backup on the way. Sherlock E-T-A thirty minutes.

The view blurs, spins then focuses on:

- Police Cars in front of a tall apartment building--SNAP

.ON THE STREET

MITCH SAWYER’s Hands fiddle with the camera’s controls trying to advance the film, then popping the back open... 

MITCH (V.O.)
No other breaking stories.

REVEAL: there’s NO FILM IN THE CAMERA. 

MITCH (O.C.)
Shit.

A NASHVILLE TRIBUNE PASS with the title “PHOTOJOURNALIST”, hangs from around his neck beside his camera. He unzips then digs through his camera bag.

MITCH (V.O.)
And having it in the paper on Sunday, would mean I had follow-ups to write all week long.

Spots on his rumpled oversize chambray button-down and equally rumpled jeans are runoff from the rain falling off his NASHVILLE SOUNDS BALL CAP. 

MITCH (V.O.)
The Chin Murder came to me perfectly packaged and ready to sell.

Mitch is not happy. Turning away from the scene, a neon sign buzzes to life in the pre-dawn: 

>**_DRUGS - FILM - SODA_**”<

Mitch walks toward it.

EXT. NASHVILLE, TN - EARLY MORNING

Exiting the shop, Loading, advancing a roll of film after stuffing several others in his camera bag, more POLICE CARS have now joined the two that were in the parking lot.

MITCH (V.O.)
Of course I’d never tell that to anyone other than another journalist.

We follow Mitch as he zeros in on HUDDLED UNIFORMED OFFICERS obscuring someone shorter giving orders.

MITCH (V.O.)
Because that would mean I’d have to give up my source.

From the camera bag: a micro-sized cassette voice recorder--Mitch switches it into VOICE ACTIVATED mode. 

MITCH
This is MITCH SAWYER with the Nashville Tribune and I’m at 1880 BELCOURT AVENUE. It is 
seven-ten AM on the nineteenth of August, nineteen ninety--

TOMMIE (O.S.)
You can’t be here.

HUDDLED UNIFORMED OFFICERS break to reveal a PLAINCLOTHES DETECTIVE wearing a name badge that reads “DET. TOMMIE HAMPTON” (50’s F, black, Butch-adjacent, Jeans, T-shirt that reads “METRO POLICE”, comfortable shoes with ZERO makeup).

MITCH
What’d you catch? 

TOMMIE
I know you want that front page but you CANNOT be here.

Between them, we catch sight of the billboard for the church again.

MITCH
This many cops. And on your day off... It’s gotta be big.

TOMMIE
Wait, Did your mom--?!

MITCH
So it was a murder?

TOMMIE
I didn’t say that--

Tommie looks at the OTHER COPS working the scene.

TOMMIE
Stihlmeyer?!

A young UNIFORMED COP (Stihlmeyer) breaks away from holding the line to receive new instructions.

TOMMIE
See that nobody gets in without a badge. Period.

STIHLMEYER
(upturned middle finger)
Suck it, paper boy.

Mitch snaps a photo. 

TOMMIE
(to Mitch)
You will not under any circumstances be getting into this building.

TOMMIE turns and enters the building; Mitch turns and walks away.

INT. APARTMENT BUILDING - EIGHTH FLOOR HALLWAY - DAY

A DING from the elevator bell as the doors open and TOMMIE emerges.

MITCH (O.C.)
You really sold that. 

Mitch waits on her holding a pad and pen.

MITCH
I mean, CHILLS! Seriously.

TOMMIE^
(into her walkie talkie)
STIHLMEYER, dispatch more uniforms to secure the other entrances to the building, please.

STIHLMEYER
(from Tommie’s walkie-talkie)
Roger that. 

MITCH
(stopping her)
You and I both know that if it’s big, you gonna lose control of the story real quick. They ain’t about to let a--

She gives him a DON’T YOU SAY IT look.

MITCH
(slowly)
**JUNIOR** Deputy take a case if it’s big.
(beat)
I’m giving you the opportunity to control the story. 

They stop for TWO DAVIDSON COUNTY CORONER EMPLOYEES--written across their backs--pushing a gurney with a BLACK BODY BAG.  Tommie gives in.

TOMMIE
Uniforms arrived on scene after reports of shots fired. The door to the apartment was open when they arrived.

Mitch covertly gets a photo of the CORONER EMPLOYEES as they push the gurney onto the elevator.

TOMMIE
You can’t go into the apartment. Even when they’re done collecting evidence.

.MITCH'S NIKON

- The FORENSICS TEAM inside the apartment--SNAP

- the place is a shambles--SNAP.

.EIGHTH FLOOR HALLWAY

Holding Mitch back...

TOMMIE
I have to be able to testify in court that your foot didn't cross that line.

TOMMIE moves; Mitch, careful to keep his foot right at the edge of the hallway, but not inside--points his camera. 

.MITCH'S NIKON

- A poster on the wall askew--BRUCE LEE'S ENTER THE DRAGON--SNAP

- A WORN BIBLE cast aside on the floor--SNAP-

- SHATTERED JIMMY CHIN AND DOLLY PARTON FRAMED PHOTO SURROUNDED BY BROKEN GLASS--Dolly is squeezing the tightly-flexed arm-muscle of the Asian teenager--SNAP

.EIGHT FLOOR HALLWAY

MITCH
(she shushes him)
Jimmy Chin Lee????!!!!

TOMMIE
Nobody's identified the body--

MITCH
Jimmy Chin Lee is dead or--?

TOMMIE
We don’t know because Nobody’s. Identified. The. Body.

MITCH
(writing furiously)
Asian male?

TOMMIE
"Features consistent."

MITCH
“Believed to be”--

TOMMIE
"Suspected to be.”--It could be a cousin or--

Mitch stops writing.

MITCH
Who do *you* think it is?

TOMMIE
You can't quote me until we tell the family.

MITCH
I am NOT THAT KIND--

TOMMIE
(under her breath)
I AM NOT HEARIN’ YOU AGREE--

MITCH
Fine. Not until you’ve--

TOMMIE
(grimly)
It's him.

Mitch drops to a knee and shoots in rapid succession--

CROSS TO:

INT. NASHVILLE TRIBUNE - DARKROOM - DAY

A contact sheet of the photos Mitch took dries on a clip-M.SAWYER written in grease pencil--the photo of the officer flipping the bird featuring prominently among them. 

A cigarette hangs off the mouth of a GRIZZLED OLD PHOTO EDITOR pulling contact sheets into a folder, onto a stack of folders.

Putting out the cigarette in an ashtray, GRIZZLED OLD PHOTO EDITOR carries the stack of contact sheets into...

INT. NASHVILLE TRIBUNE - PRESSROOM - CONTINUOUS

GRIZZLED OLD PHOTO EDITOR passes desk after desk of people typing on keyboards attached to large LED screens.

Newsroom activity buzzes around him as MITCH sits at one of the desks typing.

ON THE COMPUTER SCREEN: **...NO SUSPECTS OR MOTIVE.**

The GRIZZLED OLD PHOTO EDITOR tosses the photos onto Mitch's desk and continues on without speaking to him: He's got better things to do.

The photos slip out the folder on the desk.

MITCH
(without stopping typing)
Thanks.

From across the room:

DARLITA
TEN MINUTES TO DEADLINE.

MITCH glances at the wall... ten minutes until five.

An empty bottle of WILD TURKEY drops into Mitch’s trash bin.

MITCH
Don’t put that there.

DECK LAYTON (50’s, M, white, thick & chunky; crew cut, Sans-a-belt pants and a short-sleeve dress shirt) moves the empty to another desk’s trash bin, sipping from a TENNESSEE VOLUNTEERS coffee mug that most likely contains very little coffee.

DECK
He was amazing. And a great guy too.

COPYWRITER #1
(from farther away)
TEN MINUTES, EVERYONE.

Deck sits beside Mitch’s desk flipping through contact sheets, while Mitch types.

DECK
(slurring speech)  
Forget your “Bart Starr”’s and “Kenny Stabler”’s--

MITCH
--I have no idea who those people are--

DECK
--And you can forget your Brett Favres too--

MITCH
Favre is the one from the underwear photos in GQ, right?

Deck uses a grease pencil to circle the SHATTERED JIMMY CHIN AND DOLLY PARTON FRAMED PHOTO SURROUNDED BY BROKEN GLASS, initials his approval.

DECK
All you need to know is “Jimmy Chin Lee.” That’s your front page.

Mitch reacts to Deck’s bourbon breath.

MITCH
What I need is to finish my story on Jimmy Chin Lee or I won’t make the front page.

DECK
Your story is the only one anyone’s going to be reading tomorrow. You know what made him different?

MITCH
I've got a real shot here-so help me God--if you keep me--

DECK
Mathematics.

Mitch sighs and stops typing. There’s no getting out of this.

Out of the corner of his eye spotting DARLITA (40's, F, Latina. Curvy) typing furiously. Darlita’s face says, "Disturb me at your peril."

MITCH
Please don't go down this road--

DECK
This might sound a little crazy and I’m not being racial or nothin, seein’ how he was Oriental--Asian--whatever--

DARLITA
(from across the room)
We discussed this, Deck.

DECK
I wasn't--

DARLITA^
We. Have. An. Agreement. What was the agreement?

DECK
(chastised)
That white people should be the recipient of information about other races and not the origin.

DARLITA
And why is that?

DECK
Do we have to do this every--

DARLITA^
And. Why. Is. That?!

DECK
Because it reduces my credibility to people of color who know the facts.

DARLITA
(looking at him over her glasses, suspiciously)
Um-huh.
(back to typing)

DECK
(under his breath)
Jimmy Chin had everything that happened on the field--all the movements of the linebackers and his own linemen--reduced to numbers.
(points to his temple)

MITCH
If he was so great, Why was he staying in college another year? Why not do the draft?

DECK
I never got an interview. I never got to ask him.

MITCH
That the angle for your obit? “He was Asian and good at math”?

DECK
(beat)
Well, not now. 

Deck, exit. Mitch goes back to typing. 

DARLITA
THREE MINUTES!!! 

COPYWRITER #1
THREE MINUTES!!!

Mitch moves the cursor to a "button” on the screen and hits return. The screen responds with "SUBMITTING...SUBMITTED!”.

.FULLSCREEN

The Nashville Tribune masthead and underneath Mitch’s photo with the headline: ALL-STAR QUARTERBACK SLAIN

>FADE TO BLACK

.TITLE CARD



>**_KILL THE QUARTERBACK_**<


## FRONT PAGE SEQUENCE END

===

